Title:
Daedalus — Autonomous Claude Code Agent Framework (cron + persistent state)

Type:
GitHub Tool

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
Daedalus is a framework that runs Anthropic’s Claude Code non-interactively on a schedule (cron) to act as a long-running autonomous coding/ops agent. It solves the “stateless session” problem by persisting context and progress in a set of markdown state files (checkpoint, tasks, worklog, questions, lessons-learned) that are resumed each run. The core technique is checkpoint-based session handoff (“save game”) combined with file-based task management and a fixed multi-step autonomous workflow prompt. It includes PID management and stale-session detection to prevent overlapping/zombie runs, plus optional Pushover notifications for human-in-the-loop Q&A. Useful for engineers, red team toolsmiths, and security researchers who want an autonomous agent to continuously iterate on a repo, run tests, and manage a backlog with minimal supervision. Interesting because it operationalizes LLM autonomy with simple, auditable primitives (files + git) rather than a database or complex orchestration stack.

Technical Focus:
- Cron-driven autonomous agent execution (Claude Code `-p` non-interactive mode)
- Checkpointing / session handoff via persistent markdown state
- File-based task lifecycle management (proposed → backlog → in progress → done → archive)
- Human-in-the-loop workflow using questions.md + push notifications (Pushover)
- PID locking, stale process detection, and log rotation
- Git-friendly, auditable state and workflow prompts (CLAUDE.md, prompts/*.md)

Use Cases:
- Run an autonomous “daily” coding agent to implement tasks, refactor, and run tests on a repo
- Maintain a persistent research/worklog and lessons-learned knowledge base across sessions
- Continuous code review or maintenance runs using custom prompt files (e.g., review.md)
- Human escalation workflow for decisions/blocked steps via push notifications
- Safe unattended operation with stale-session killing and log retention controls

Keywords:
Claude Code, autonomous agent, cron, checkpointing, session handoff, persistent memory, markdown state, tasks.md, worklog.md, questions.md, lessons-learned.md, PID management, stale process detection, Pushover, non-interactive LLM, prompts, run-daily.sh, git workflow, log rotation, human-in-the-loop